<div class="r1"><input type="radio" name="q21665:34_answer" disabled="disabled" value="1" id="q21665:34_answer1" aria-labelledby="q21665:34_answer1_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:34_answer1_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">b. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">Deployment-time configuration requires recompiling the system for every change.</div></div> </div>
<div class="r0"><input type="radio" name="q21665:34_answer" disabled="disabled" value="2" id="q21665:34_answer2" aria-labelledby="q21665:34_answer2_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:34_answer2_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">c. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">Design-time configuration is performed by the developing organization to create a new system; deployment-time configuration is performed by customers/consultants using embedded configuration data.</div></div> </div>
<div class="r1"><input type="radio" name="q21665:34_answer" disabled="disabled" value="3" id="q21665:34_answer3" aria-labelledby="q21665:34_answer3_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:34_answer3_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">d. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">Design-time configuration happens after installation; deployment-time configuration happens before coding.</div></div> </div>
