<div class="r1"><input type="radio" name="q21665:102_answer" disabled="disabled" value="1" id="q21665:102_answer1" aria-labelledby="q21665:102_answer1_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:102_answer1_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">b. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">Because component testing is illegal in most procurement contracts.</div></div> </div>
<div class="r0"><input type="radio" name="q21665:102_answer" disabled="disabled" value="2" id="q21665:102_answer2" aria-labelledby="q21665:102_answer2_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:102_answer2_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">c. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">Because reliability is only a software concept and cannot be applied to systems with hardware.</div></div> </div>
<div class="r1"><input type="radio" name="q21665:102_answer" disabled="disabled" value="3" id="q21665:102_answer3" aria-labelledby="q21665:102_answer3_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:102_answer3_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">d. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1"><span class="filter_mathjaxloader_equation">Because unforeseen interactions and dependency chains can introduce new failure modes, so <span class="nolink"><mjx-container class="MathJax CtxtMenu_Attached_0" jax="CHTML" tabindex="0" ctxtmenu_counter="8" style="font-size: 120.2%; position: relative;"><mjx-math class="MJX-TEX" aria-hidden="true"><mjx-msub><mjx-mi class="mjx-i"><mjx-c class="mjx-c1D445 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi><mjx-script style="vertical-align: -0.15em;"><mjx-texatom size="s" texclass="ORD"><mjx-mi class="mjx-i"><mjx-c class="mjx-c1D460 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi><mjx-mi class="mjx-i"><mjx-c class="mjx-c1D466 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi><mjx-mi class="mjx-i"><mjx-c class="mjx-c1D460 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi></mjx-texatom></mjx-script></mjx-msub></mjx-math><mjx-assistive-mml unselectable="on" display="inline"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msub><mi>R</mi><mrow data-mjx-texclass="ORD"><mi>s</mi><mi>y</mi><mi>s</mi></mrow></msub></math></mjx-assistive-mml></mjx-container></span> reflects more than isolated component behavior.</span></div></div> </div>
</div></fieldset></div><div class="outcome clearfix"><h4 class="accesshide">Geri bildirim</h4><div class="feedback"><div class="generalfeedback"><div class="clearfix"><p>Unexpected interactions and fault propagation across dependencies can produce failures not visible at component level.</p></div></div><div class="rightanswer">Doğru cevap: <span class="filter_mathjaxloader_equation">Because unforeseen interactions and dependency chains can introduce new failure modes, so <span class="nolink"><mjx-container class="MathJax CtxtMenu_Attached_0" jax="CHTML" tabindex="0" ctxtmenu_counter="9" style="font-size: 120.2%; position: relative;"><mjx-math class="MJX-TEX" aria-hidden="true"><mjx-msub><mjx-mi class="mjx-i"><mjx-c class="mjx-c1D445 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi><mjx-script style="vertical-align: -0.15em;"><mjx-texatom size="s" texclass="ORD"><mjx-mi class="mjx-i"><mjx-c class="mjx-c1D460 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi><mjx-mi class="mjx-i"><mjx-c class="mjx-c1D466 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi><mjx-mi class="mjx-i"><mjx-c class="mjx-c1D460 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi></mjx-texatom></mjx-script></mjx-msub></mjx-math><mjx-assistive-mml unselectable="on" display="inline"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msub><mi>R</mi><mrow data-mjx-texclass="ORD"><mi>s</mi><mi>y</mi><mi>s</mi></mrow></msub></math></mjx-assistive-mml></mjx-container></span> reflects more than isolated component behavior.</span></div></div></div></div></div><div id="question-21665-103" class="que multichoice interactive notanswered"><div class="info"><h3 class="no">Soru <span class="qno">103</span></h3><div class="state">Cevaplanmadı</div><div class="grade">1,00 üzerinden puanlanmış</div><div class="questionflag editable" id="yui_3_18_1_1_1767644350614_630"><input type="hidden" name="q21665:103_:flagged" value="0"><input type="hidden" value="qaid=530997&amp;qubaid=21665&amp;qid=11570&amp;slot=103&amp;checksum=30a7e57efc34b100bae32bae805ab957&amp;sesskey=bsAI63OWde&amp;newstate=" class="questionflagpostdata">
<input type="hidden" class="questionflagvalue" id="q21665:103_:flaggedcheckbox" name="q21665:103_:flagged" value="0"><a tabindex="0" class="aabtn" role="button" aria-pressed="false" aria-label="İşaretli" title="İlerisi için bu soruyu işaretle"><img class="questionflagimage" src="https://online-learning2025-2026.gidatarim.edu.tr/theme/image.php/academi/core/1762167339/i/unflagged" alt="">Soruyu işaretle</a></div></div><div class="content"><div class="formulation clearfix"><h4 class="accesshide">Soru metini</h4><input type="hidden" name="q21665:103_:sequencecheck" value="2"><div class="qtext"><div class="clearfix"><span class="filter_mathjaxloader_equation"><p>Let component reliabilities be <span class="nolink"><mjx-container class="MathJax CtxtMenu_Attached_0" jax="CHTML" tabindex="0" ctxtmenu_counter="10" style="font-size: 120.2%; position: relative;"><mjx-math class="MJX-TEX" aria-hidden="true"><mjx-msub><mjx-mi class="mjx-i"><mjx-c class="mjx-c1D445 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi><mjx-script style="vertical-align: -0.15em;"><mjx-mn class="mjx-n" size="s"><mjx-c class="mjx-c31"></mjx-c></mjx-mn></mjx-script></mjx-msub><mjx-mo class="mjx-n"><mjx-c class="mjx-c2C"></mjx-c></mjx-mo><mjx-msub space="2"><mjx-mi class="mjx-i"><mjx-c class="mjx-c1D445 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi><mjx-script style="vertical-align: -0.15em;"><mjx-mn class="mjx-n" size="s"><mjx-c class="mjx-c32"></mjx-c></mjx-mn></mjx-script></mjx-msub><mjx-mo class="mjx-n"><mjx-c class="mjx-c2C"></mjx-c></mjx-mo><mjx-mo class="mjx-n" space="2"><mjx-c class="mjx-c2026"></mjx-c></mjx-mo><mjx-mo class="mjx-n" space="2"><mjx-c class="mjx-c2C"></mjx-c></mjx-mo><mjx-msub space="2"><mjx-mi class="mjx-i"><mjx-c class="mjx-c1D445 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi><mjx-script style="vertical-align: -0.15em;"><mjx-mi class="mjx-i" size="s"><mjx-c class="mjx-c1D45B TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi></mjx-script></mjx-msub></mjx-math><mjx-assistive-mml unselectable="on" display="inline"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>,</mo><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>,</mo><mo>…</mo><mo>,</mo><msub><mi>R</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></math></mjx-assistive-mml></mjx-container></span>. Why might the overall system reliability <span class="nolink"><mjx-container class="MathJax CtxtMenu_Attached_0" jax="CHTML" tabindex="0" ctxtmenu_counter="11" style="font-size: 120.2%; position: relative;"><mjx-math class="MJX-TEX" aria-hidden="true"><mjx-msub><mjx-mi class="mjx-i"><mjx-c class="mjx-c1D445 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi><mjx-script style="vertical-align: -0.15em;"><mjx-texatom size="s" texclass="ORD"><mjx-mi class="mjx-i"><mjx-c class="mjx-c1D460 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi><mjx-mi class="mjx-i"><mjx-c class="mjx-c1D466 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi><mjx-mi class="mjx-i"><mjx-c class="mjx-c1D460 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi></mjx-texatom></mjx-script></mjx-msub></mjx-math><mjx-assistive-mml unselectable="on" display="inline"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msub><mi>R</mi><mrow data-mjx-texclass="ORD"><mi>s</mi><mi>y</mi><mi>s</mi></mrow></msub></math></mjx-assistive-mml></mjx-container></span> <em>not</em> be accurately predicted by simply combining individual reliabilities?</p></span></div></div><fieldset class="ablock no-overflow visual-scroll-x"><legend class="prompt h6 fw-normal "><span class="visually-hidden">Soru 103</span> Lütfen birini seçin:</legend><div class="answer"><div class="r0"><input type="radio" name="q21665:103_answer" disabled="disabled" value="0" id="q21665:103_answer0" aria-labelledby="q21665:103_answer0_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:103_answer0_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">a. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">Because reliability is only a software concept and cannot be applied to systems with hardware.</div></div> </div>
<div class="r1"><input type="radio" name="q21665:103_answer" disabled="disabled" value="1" id="q21665:103_answer1" aria-labelledby="q21665:103_answer1_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:103_answer1_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">b. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">Because component testing is illegal in most procurement contracts.</div></div> </div>
<div class="r0"><input type="radio" name="q21665:103_answer" disabled="disabled" value="2" id="q21665:103_answer2" aria-labelledby="q21665:103_answer2_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:103_answer2_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">c. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1"><span class="filter_mathjaxloader_equation">Because <span class="nolink"><mjx-container class="MathJax CtxtMenu_Attached_0" jax="CHTML" tabindex="0" ctxtmenu_counter="12" style="font-size: 120.2%; position: relative;"><mjx-math class="MJX-TEX" aria-hidden="true"><mjx-msub><mjx-mi class="mjx-i"><mjx-c class="mjx-c1D445 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi><mjx-script style="vertical-align: -0.15em;"><mjx-texatom size="s" texclass="ORD"><mjx-mi class="mjx-i"><mjx-c class="mjx-c1D460 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi><mjx-mi class="mjx-i"><mjx-c class="mjx-c1D466 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi><mjx-mi class="mjx-i"><mjx-c class="mjx-c1D460 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi></mjx-texatom></mjx-script></mjx-msub></mjx-math><mjx-assistive-mml unselectable="on" display="inline"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msub><mi>R</mi><mrow data-mjx-texclass="ORD"><mi>s</mi><mi>y</mi><mi>s</mi></mrow></msub></math></mjx-assistive-mml></mjx-container></span> always equals <span class="nolink"><mjx-container class="MathJax CtxtMenu_Attached_0" jax="CHTML" tabindex="0" ctxtmenu_counter="13" style="font-size: 120.2%; position: relative;"><mjx-math class="MJX-TEX" aria-hidden="true"><mjx-msub><mjx-mi class="mjx-i"><mjx-c class="mjx-c1D445 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi><mjx-script style="vertical-align: -0.15em;"><mjx-mn class="mjx-n" size="s"><mjx-c class="mjx-c31"></mjx-c></mjx-mn></mjx-script></mjx-msub><mjx-mo class="mjx-n" space="3"><mjx-c class="mjx-c2B"></mjx-c></mjx-mo><mjx-msub space="3"><mjx-mi class="mjx-i"><mjx-c class="mjx-c1D445 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi><mjx-script style="vertical-align: -0.15em;"><mjx-mn class="mjx-n" size="s"><mjx-c class="mjx-c32"></mjx-c></mjx-mn></mjx-script></mjx-msub><mjx-mo clas