<div class="r1"><input type="radio" name="q21665:103_answer" disabled="disabled" value="3" id="q21665:103_answer3" aria-labelledby="q21665:103_answer3_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:103_answer3_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">d. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1"><span class="filter_mathjaxloader_equation">Because unforeseen interactions and dependency chains can introduce new failure modes, so <span class="nolink"><mjx-container class="MathJax CtxtMenu_Attached_0" jax="CHTML" tabindex="0" ctxtmenu_counter="14" style="font-size: 120.2%; position: relative;"><mjx-math class="MJX-TEX" aria-hidden="true"><mjx-msub><mjx-mi class="mjx-i"><mjx-c class="mjx-c1D445 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi><mjx-script style="vertical-align: -0.15em;"><mjx-texatom size="s" texclass="ORD"><mjx-mi class="mjx-i"><mjx-c class="mjx-c1D460 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi><mjx-mi class="mjx-i"><mjx-c class="mjx-c1D466 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi><mjx-mi class="mjx-i"><mjx-c class="mjx-c1D460 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi></mjx-texatom></mjx-script></mjx-msub></mjx-math><mjx-assistive-mml unselectable="on" display="inline"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msub><mi>R</mi><mrow data-mjx-texclass="ORD"><mi>s</mi><mi>y</mi><mi>s</mi></mrow></msub></math></mjx-assistive-mml></mjx-container></span> reflects more than isolated component behavior.</span></div></div> </div>
</div></fieldset></div><div class="outcome clearfix"><h4 class="accesshide">Geri bildirim</h4><div class="feedback"><div class="generalfeedback"><div class="clearfix"><p>Unexpected interactions and fault propagation across dependencies can produce failures not visible at component level.</p></div></div><div class="rightanswer">Doğru cevap: <span class="filter_mathjaxloader_equation">Because unforeseen interactions and dependency chains can introduce new failure modes, so <span class="nolink"><mjx-container class="MathJax CtxtMenu_Attached_0" jax="CHTML" tabindex="0" ctxtmenu_counter="15" style="font-size: 120.2%; position: relative;"><mjx-math class="MJX-TEX" aria-hidden="true"><mjx-msub><mjx-mi class="mjx-i"><mjx-c class="mjx-c1D445 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi><mjx-script style="vertical-align: -0.15em;"><mjx-texatom size="s" texclass="ORD"><mjx-mi class="mjx-i"><mjx-c class="mjx-c1D460 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi><mjx-mi class="mjx-i"><mjx-c class="mjx-c1D466 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi><mjx-mi class="mjx-i"><mjx-c class="mjx-c1D460 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi></mjx-texatom></mjx-script></mjx-msub></mjx-math><mjx-assistive-mml unselectable="on" display="inline"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msub><mi>R</mi><mrow data-mjx-texclass="ORD"><mi>s</mi><mi>y</mi><mi>s</mi></mrow></msub></math></mjx-assistive-mml></mjx-container></span> reflects more than isolated component behavior.</span></div></div></div></div></div><div id="question-21665-104" class="que multichoice interactive notanswered"><div class="info"><h3 class="no">Soru <span class="qno">104</span></h3><div class="state">Cevaplanmadı</div><div class="grade">1,00 üzerinden puanlanmış</div><div class="questionflag editable" id="yui_3_18_1_1_1767644350614_636"><input type="hidden" name="q21665:104_:flagged" value="0"><input type="hidden" value="qaid=530998&amp;qubaid=21665&amp;qid=11484&amp;slot=104&amp;checksum=2c3b57b0ce9345d873144e50119a7172&amp;sesskey=bsAI63OWde&amp;newstate=" class="questionflagpostdata">
<input type="hidden" class="questionflagvalue" id="q21665:104_:flaggedcheckbox" name="q21665:104_:flagged" value="0"><a tabindex="0" class="aabtn" role="button" aria-pressed="false" aria-label="İşaretli" title="İlerisi için bu soruyu işaretle"><img class="questionflagimage" src="https://online-learning2025-2026.gidatarim.edu.tr/theme/image.php/academi/core/1762167339/i/unflagged" alt="">Soruyu işaretle</a></div></div><div class="content"><div class="formulation clearfix"><h4 class="accesshide">Soru metini</h4><input type="hidden" name="q21665:104_:sequencecheck" value="2"><div class="qtext"><div class="clearfix"><p>Which statement best explains the relationship between a <b>threat</b> and an <b>attack</b>?</p></div></div><fieldset class="ablock no-overflow visual-scroll-x"><legend class="prompt h6 fw-normal "><span class="visually-hidden">Soru 104</span> Lütfen birini seçin:</legend><div class="answer"><div class="r0"><input type="radio" name="q21665:104_answer" disabled="disabled" value="0" id="q21665:104_answer0" aria-labelledby="q21665:104_answer0_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:104_answer0_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">a. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">A threat is always accidental; an attack is always unintentional.</div></div> </div>
<div class="r1"><input type="radio" name="q21665:104_answer" disabled="disabled" value="1" id="q21665:104_answer1" aria-labelledby="q21665:104_answer1_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:104_answer1_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">b. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">An attack is a protective measure; a threat is the control that reduces vulnerability.</div></div> </div>
<div class="r0"><input type="radio" name="q21665:104_answer" disabled="disabled" value="2" id="q21665:104_answer2" aria-labelledby="q21665:104_answer2_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:104_answer2_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">c. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">A threat and an attack mean the same thing in risk analysis.</div></div> </div>
<div class="r1"><input type="radio" name="q21665:104_answer" disabled="disabled" value="3" id="q21665:104_answer3" aria-labelledby="q21665:104_answer3_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:104_answer3_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">d. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">A threat is the potential for harm; an attack is an exploitation of a vulnerability that attempts to cause damage.</div></div> </div>
</div></fieldset></div><div class="outcome clearfix"><h4 class="accesshide">Geri bildirim</h4><div class="feedback"><div class="generalfeedback"><div class="clearfix"><p>A threat is a circumstance with potential for harm; an attack is the exploitation of a vulnerability (often deliberate) that may realize that harm.</p></div></div><div class="rightanswer">Doğru cevap: A threat is the potential for harm; an attack is an exploitation of a vulnerability that attempts to cause damage.</div></div></div></div></div><div id="question-21665-105" class="que multichoice interactive notanswered"><div class="info"><h3 class="no">Soru <span class="qno">105</span></h3><div class="state">Cevaplanmadı</div><div class="grade">1,00 üzerinden puanlanmış</div><div class="questionflag editable" id="yui_3_18_1_1_1767644350614_642"><input type="hidden" name="q21665:105_:flagged" value="0"><input type="hidden" value="qaid=530999&amp;qubaid=21665&amp;qid=11552&amp;slot=105&amp;checksum=b54cb2072f2f5b8087cb18ddf9d1ea17&amp;sesskey=bsAI63OWde&amp;newstate=" class="questionflagpostdata">
<input type="hidden" class="questionflagvalue" id="q21665:105_:flaggedcheckbox" name="q21665:105_:flagged" value="0"><a tabindex="0" class="aabtn" role="button" aria-pressed="false" aria-label="İşaretli" title="İlerisi için bu soruyu işaretle"><img class="questionflagimage" src="https://online-learning2025-2026.gidatarim.edu.tr/theme/image.php/academi/core/1762167339/i/unflagged" alt="">Soruyu işaretle</a></div></div><div class="content"><div class="formulation clearfix"><h4 class="accesshide">Soru metini</h4><input type="hidden" name="q21665:105_:sequencecheck" value="2"><div class="qtext"><div class="clearfix"><p>Which statement best explains <em>failure propagation</em> in complex systems?</p></div></div><fieldset class="ablock no-overflow visual-scroll-x"><legend class="prompt h6 fw-normal "><span class="visually-hidden">Soru 105</span> Lütfen birini seçin:</legend><div class="answer"><div class="r0"><input type="radio" name="q21665:105_answer" disabled="disabled" value="0" id="q21665:105_answer0" aria-labelledby="q21665:105_answer0_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:105_answer0_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">a. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">A fault in one component can trigger incorrect behavior in dependent components, potentially cascading into a system failure.</div></div> </div>
<div class="r1"><input type="radio" name="q21665:105_answer" disabled="disabled" value="1" id="q21665:105_answer1" aria-labelledby="q21665:105_answer1_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:105_answer1_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">b. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">Failures only occur independently, so one failing component cannot affect others.</div></div> </div>
<div class="r0"><input type="radio" name="q21665:105_answer" disabled="disabled" value="2" id="q21665:105_answer2" aria-labelledby="q21665:105_answer2_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:105_answer2_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">c. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">Propagation can happen only in hardware, never in software or operations.</div></div> </div>
<div class="r1"><input type="radio" name="q21665:105_answer" disabled="disabled" value="3" id="q21665:105_answer3" aria-labelledby="q21665:105_answer3_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:105_answer3_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">d. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">Propagation is prevented automatically by using off-the-shelf components.</div></div> </div>
</div></fieldset></div><div class="outcome clearfix"><h4 class="accesshide">Geri bildirim</h4><div class="feedback"><div class="generalfeedback"><div class="clearfix"><p>Because components are interdependent, faults can spread across hardware, software, and human operation levels.</p></div></div><div class="rightanswer">Doğru cevap: A fault in one component can trigger incorrect behavior in dependent components, potentially cascading into a system failure.</div></div></div></div></div><div id="question-21665-106" class="que multichoice interactive notanswered"><div class="info"><h3 class="no">Soru <span class="qno">106</span></h3><div class="state">Cevaplanmadı</div><div class="grade">1,00 üzerinden puanlanmış</div><div class="questionflag editable" id="yui_3_18_1_1_1767644350614_648"><input type="hidden" name="q21665:106_:flagged" value="0"><input type="hidden" value="qaid=531000&amp;qubaid=21665&amp;qid=11571&amp;slot=106&amp;checksum=ca6ca243fa0d2ef066b45a569f82a17d&amp;sesskey=bsAI63OWde&amp;newstate=" class="questionflagpostdata">
<input type="hidden" class="questionflagvalue" id="q21665:106_:flaggedcheckbox" name="q21665:106_:flagged" value="0"><a tabindex="0" class="aabtn" role="button" aria-pressed="false" aria-label="İşaretli" title="İlerisi için bu soruyu işaretle"><img class="questionflagimage" src="https://online-learning2025-2026.gidatarim.edu.tr/theme/image.php/academi/core/1762167339/i/unflagged" alt="">Soruyu işaretle</a></div></div><div class="content"><div class="formulation clearfix"><h4 class="accesshide">Soru metini</h4><input type="hidden" name="q21665:106_:sequencecheck" value="2"><div class="qtext"><div class="clearfix"><p>Which statement best explains <em>failure propagation</em> in complex systems?</p></div></div><fieldset class="ablock no-overflow visual-scroll-x"><legend class="prompt h6 fw-normal "><span class="visually-hidden">Soru 106</span> Lütfen birini seçin:</legend><div class="answer"><div class="r0"><input type="radio" name="q21665:106_answer" disabled="disabled" value="0" id="q21665:106_answer0" aria-labelledby="q21665:106_answer0_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:106_answer0_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">a. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">Propagation can happen only in hardware, never in software or operations.</div></div> </div>
<div class="r1"><input type="radio" name="q21665:106_answer" disabled="disabled" value="1" id="q21665:106_answer1" aria-labelledby="q21665:106_answer1_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:106_answer1_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">b. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">A fault in one component can trigger incorrect behavior in dependent components, potentially cascading into a system failure.</div></div> </div>
<div class="r0"><input type="radio" name="q21665:106_answer" disabled="disabled" value="2" id="q21665:106_answer2" aria-labelledby="q21665:106_answer2_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:106_answer2_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">c. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">Propagation is prevented automatically by using off-the-shelf components.</div></div> </div>
<div class="r1"><input type="radio" name="q21665:106_answer" disabled="disabled" value="3" id="q21665:106_answer3" aria-labelledby="q21665:106_answer3_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:106_answer3_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">d. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">Failures only occur independently, so one failing component cannot affect others.</div></div> </div>
</div></fieldset></div><div class="outcome clearfix"><h4 class="accesshide">Geri bildirim</h4><div class="feedback"><div class="generalfeedback"><div class="clearfix"><p>Because components are interdependent, faults can spread across hardware, software, and human operation levels.</p></div></div><div class="rightanswer">Doğru cevap: A fault in one component can trigger incorrect behavior in dependent components, potentially cascading into a system failure.</div></div></div></div></div><div id="question-21665-107" class="que multichoice interactive notanswered"><div class="info"><h3 class="no">Soru <span class="qno">107</span></h3><div class="state">Cevaplanmadı</div><div class="grade">1,00 üzerinden puanlanmış</div><div class="questionflag editable" id="yui_3_18_1_1_1767644350614_654"><input type="hidden" name="q21665:107_:flagged" value="0"><input type="hidden" value="qaid=531001&amp;qubaid=21665&amp;qid=11485&amp;slot=107&amp;checksum=eac1fd855a209603631cdac10ca848a3&amp;sesskey=bsAI63OWde&amp;newstate=" class="questionflagpostdata">
<input type="hidden" class="questionflagvalue" id="q21665:107_:flaggedcheckbox" name="q21665:107_:flagged" value="0"><a tabindex="0" class="aabtn" role="button" aria-pressed="false" aria-label="İşaretli" title="İlerisi için bu soruyu işaretle"><img class="questionflagimage" src="https://online-learning2025-2026.gidatarim.edu.tr/theme/image.php/academi/core/1762167339/i/unflagged" alt="">Soruyu işaretle</a></div></div><div class="content"><div class="formulation clearfix"><h4 class="accesshide">Soru metini</h4><input type="hidden" name="q21665:107_:sequencecheck" value="2"><div class="qtext"><div class="clearfix"><p>Which option is the best example of a <b>control</b> in security engineering?</p></div></div><fieldset class="ablock no-overflow visual-scroll-x"><legend class="prompt h6 fw-normal "><span class="visually-hidden">Soru 107</span> Lütfen birini seçin:</legend><div class="answer"><div class="r0"><input type="radio" name="q21665:107_answer" disabled="disabled" value="0" id="q21665:107_answer0" aria-labelledby="q21665:107_answer0_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:107_answer0_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">a. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">Encrypting sensitive files so unauthorized users cannot read them.</div></div> </div>
<div class="r1"><input type="radio" name="q21665:107_answer" disabled="disabled" value="1" id="q21665:107_answer1" aria-labelledby="q21665:107_answer1_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:107_answer1_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">b. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">A weak password policy that allows 'password123'.</div></div> </div>
<div class="r0"><input type="radio" name="q21665:107_answer" disabled="disabled" value="2" id="q21665:107_answer2" aria-labelledby="q21665:107_answer2_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:107_answer2_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">c. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">Storing secrets in plain text to simplify debugging.</div></div> </div>
<div class="r1"><input type="radio" name="q21665:107_answer" disabled="disabled" value="3" id="q21665:107_answer3" aria-labelledby="q21665:107_answer3_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:107_answer3_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">d. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">Removing audit logs to reduce storage costs.</div></div> </div>
</div></fieldset></div><div class="outcome clearfix"><h4 class="accesshide">Geri bildirim</h4><div class="feedback"><div class="generalfeedback"><div class="clearfix"><p>A control is a protective measure that reduces vulnerability (e.g., encryption, strong password enforcement, logging).</p></div></div><div class="rightanswer">Doğru cevap: Encrypting sensitive files so unauthorized users cannot read them.</div></div></div></div></div><div id="question-21665-108" class="que multichoice interactive notanswered"><div class="info"><h3 class="no">Soru <span class="qno">108</span></h3><div class="state">Cevaplanmadı</div><div class="grade">1,00 üzerinden puanlanmış</div><div class="questionflag editable" id="yui_3_18_1_1_1767644350614_660"><input type="hidden" name="q21665:108_:flagged" value="0"><input type="hidden" value="qaid=531002&amp;qubaid=21665&amp;qid=11553&amp;slot=108&amp;checksum=57ba1cb4446c72af1aebdb2cec7b8151&amp;sesskey=bsAI63OWde&amp;newstate=" class="questionflagpostdata">
<input type="hidden" class="questionflagvalue" id="q21665:108_:flaggedcheckbox" name="q21665:108_:flagged" value="0"><a tabindex="0" class="aabtn" role="button" aria-pressed="false" aria-label="İşaretli" title="İlerisi için bu soruyu işaretle"><img class="questionflagimage" src="https://online-learning2025-2026.gidatarim.edu.tr/theme/image.php/academi/core/1762167339/i/unflagged" alt="">Soruyu işaretle</a></div></div><div class="content"><div class="formulation clearfix"><h4 class="accesshide">Soru metini</h4><input type="hidden" name="q21665:108_:sequencecheck" value="2"><div class="qtext"><div class="clearfix"><p>A deterministic system produces the same outputs for the same inputs. Why can sociotechnical systems be non-deterministic even when the software is deterministic?</p></div></div><fieldset class="ablock no-overflow visual-scroll-x"><legend class="prompt h6 fw-normal "><span class="visually-hidden">Soru 108</span> Lütfen birini seçin:</legend><div class="answer"><div class="r0"><input type="radio" name="q21665:108_answer" disabled="disabled" value="0" id="q21665:108_answer0" aria-labelledby="q21665:108_answer0_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:108_answer0_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">a. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">Because overall behavior depends partly on human actions and operational context, which may vary even under the same nominal inputs.</div></div> </div>
<div class="r1"><input type="radio" name="q21665:108_answer" disabled="disabled" value="1" id="q21665:108_answer1" aria-labelledby="q21665:108_answer1_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:108_answer1_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">b. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">Because procurement decisions automatically randomize system outputs.</div></div> </div>
<div class="r0"><input type="radio" name="q21665:108_answer" disabled="disabled" value="2" id="q21665:108_answer2" aria-labelledby="q21665:108_answer2_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:108_answer2_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">c. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">Because deterministic software is impossible to build in practice.</div></div> </div>
<div class="r1"><input type="radio" name="q21665:108_answer" disabled="disabled" value="3" id="q21665:108_answer3" aria-labelledby="q21665:108_answer3_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:108_answer3_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">d. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">Because determinism is defined only for mechanical systems, not computer systems.</div></div> </div>
</div></fieldset></div><div class="outcome clearfix"><h4 class="accesshide">Geri bildirim</h4><div class="feedback"><div class="generalfeedback"><div class="clearfix"><p>Human behavior and frequent changes to data, hardware, and procedures can make the overall system produce varying outputs.</p></div></div><div class="rightanswer">Doğru cevap: Because overall behavior depends partly on human actions and operational context, which may vary even under the same nominal inputs.</div></div></div></div></div><div id="question-21665-109" class="que multichoice interactive notanswered"><div class="info"><h3 class="no">Soru <span class="qno">109</span></h3><div class="state">Cevaplanmadı</div><div class="grade">1,00 üzerinden puanlanmış</div><div class="questionflag editable" id="yui_3_18_1_1_1767644350614_666"><input type="hidden" name="q21665:109_:flagged" value="0"><input type="hidden" value="qaid=531003&amp;qubaid=21665&amp;qid=11572&amp;slot=109&amp;checksum=8167409de5aba15fceead46b04343475&amp;sesskey=bsAI63OWde&amp;newstate=" class="questionflagpostdata">
<input type="hidden" class="questionflagvalue" id="q21665:109_:flaggedcheckbox" name="q21665:109_:flagged" value="0"><a tabindex="0" class="aabtn" role="button" aria-pressed="false" aria-label="İşaretli" title="İlerisi için bu soruyu işaretle"><img class="questionflagimage" src="https://online-learning2025-2026.gidatarim.edu.tr/theme/image.php/academi/core/1762167339/i/unflagged" alt="">Soruyu işaretle</a></div></div><div class="content"><div class="formulation clearfix"><h4 class="accesshide">Soru metini</h4><input type="hidden" name="q21665:109_:sequencecheck" value="2"><div class="qtext"><div class="clearfix"><p>A deterministic system produces the same outputs for the same inputs. Why can sociotechnical systems be non-deterministic even when the software is deterministic?</p></div></div><fieldset class="ablock no-overflow visual-scroll-x"><legend class="prompt h6 fw-normal "><span class="visually-hidden">Soru 109</span> Lütfen birini seçin:</legend><div class="answer"><div class="r0"><input type="radio" name="q21665:109_answer" disabled="disabled" value="0" id="q21665:109_answer0" aria-labelledby="q21665:109_answer0_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:109_answer0_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">a. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">Because procurement decisions automatically randomize system outputs.</div></div> </div>
