<input type="hidden" class="questionflagvalue" id="q21665:125_:flaggedcheckbox" name="q21665:125_:flagged" value="0"><a tabindex="0" class="aabtn" role="button" aria-pressed="false" aria-label="İşaretli" title="İlerisi için bu soruyu işaretle"><img class="questionflagimage" src="https://online-learning2025-2026.gidatarim.edu.tr/theme/image.php/academi/core/1762167339/i/unflagged" alt="">Soruyu işaretle</a></div></div><div class="content"><div class="formulation clearfix"><h4 class="accesshide">Soru metini</h4><input type="hidden" name="q21665:125_:sequencecheck" value="2"><div class="qtext"><div class="clearfix"><p>Which principle best reflects a cost-effective, risk-based approach to security?</p></div></div><fieldset class="ablock no-overflow visual-scroll-x"><legend class="prompt h6 fw-normal "><span class="visually-hidden">Soru 125</span> Lütfen birini seçin:</legend><div class="answer"><div class="r0"><input type="radio" name="q21665:125_answer" disabled="disabled" value="0" id="q21665:125_answer0" aria-labelledby="q21665:125_answer0_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:125_answer0_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">a. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">Do not spend more on controls than the value of the asset they protect.</div></div> </div>
<div class="r1"><input type="radio" name="q21665:125_answer" disabled="disabled" value="1" id="q21665:125_answer1" aria-labelledby="q21665:125_answer1_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:125_answer1_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">b. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">Always implement the strongest possible controls regardless of cost.</div></div> </div>
<div class="r0"><input type="radio" name="q21665:125_answer" disabled="disabled" value="2" id="q21665:125_answer2" aria-labelledby="q21665:125_answer2_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:125_answer2_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">c. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">Prioritize aesthetic UI improvements over security controls.</div></div> </div>
<div class="r1"><input type="radio" name="q21665:125_answer" disabled="disabled" value="3" id="q21665:125_answer3" aria-labelledby="q21665:125_answer3_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:125_answer3_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">d. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">Remove authentication to reduce development time.</div></div> </div>
</div></fieldset></div><div class="outcome clearfix"><h4 class="accesshide">Geri bildirim</h4><div class="feedback"><div class="generalfeedback"><div class="clearfix"><p>Security decisions should be cost-effective; it is not rational to spend more than the value of the asset being protected.</p></div></div><div class="rightanswer">Doğru cevap: Do not spend more on controls than the value of the asset they protect.</div></div></div></div></div><div id="question-21665-126" class="que multichoice interactive notanswered"><div class="info"><h3 class="no">Soru <span class="qno">126</span></h3><div class="state">Cevaplanmadı</div><div class="grade">1,00 üzerinden puanlanmış</div><div class="questionflag editable" id="yui_3_18_1_1_1767644350614_768"><input type="hidden" name="q21665:126_:flagged" value="0"><input type="hidden" value="qaid=531020&amp;qubaid=21665&amp;qid=11559&amp;slot=126&amp;checksum=fe04d2450f29ddf0241ba0c4da7fde46&amp;sesskey=bsAI63OWde&amp;newstate=" class="questionflagpostdata">
<input type="hidden" class="questionflagvalue" id="q21665:126_:flaggedcheckbox" name="q21665:126_:flagged" value="0"><a tabindex="0" class="aabtn" role="button" aria-pressed="false" aria-label="İşaretli" title="İlerisi için bu soruyu işaretle"><img class="questionflagimage" src="https://online-learning2025-2026.gidatarim.edu.tr/theme/image.php/academi/core/1762167339/i/unflagged" alt="">Soruyu işaretle</a></div></div><div class="content"><div class="formulation clearfix"><h4 class="accesshide">Soru metini</h4><input type="hidden" name="q21665:126_:sequencecheck" value="2"><div class="qtext"><div class="clearfix"><p>When a system is built specially by a supplier, why is the requirements specification often considered both a technical and a legal document?</p></div></div><fieldset class="ablock no-overflow visual-scroll-x"><legend class="prompt h6 fw-normal "><span class="visually-hidden">Soru 126</span> Lütfen birini seçin:</legend><div class="answer"><div class="r0"><input type="radio" name="q21665:126_answer" disabled="disabled" value="0" id="q21665:126_answer0" aria-labelledby="q21665:126_answer0_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:126_answer0_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">a. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">Because legal documents cannot include diagrams or models.</div></div> </div>
<div class="r1"><input type="radio" name="q21665:126_answer" disabled="disabled" value="1" id="q21665:126_answer1" aria-labelledby="q21665:126_answer1_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:126_answer1_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">b. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">Because off-the-shelf systems require detailed requirements to be used.</div></div> </div>
<div class="r0"><input type="radio" name="q21665:126_answer" disabled="disabled" value="2" id="q21665:126_answer2" aria-labelledby="q21665:126_answer2_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:126_answer2_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">c. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">Because requirements are always written by lawyers and never by engineers.</div></div> </div>
<div class="r1"><input type="radio" name="q21665:126_answer" disabled="disabled" value="3" id="q21665:126_answer3" aria-labelledby="q21665:126_answer3_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:126_answer3_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">d. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">Because the specification is part of the development contract, defining what the supplier must deliver and under what terms.</div></div> </div>
</div></fieldset></div><div class="outcome clearfix"><h4 class="accesshide">Geri bildirim</h4><div class="feedback"><div class="generalfeedback"><div class="clearfix"><p>For custom builds, requirements become part of the contract and can determine obligations and liabilities.</p></div></div><div class="rightanswer">Doğru cevap: Because the specification is part of the development contract, defining what the supplier must deliver and under what terms.</div></div></div></div></div><div id="question-21665-127" class="que multichoice interactive notanswered"><div class="info"><h3 class="no">Soru <span class="qno">127</span></h3><div class="state">Cevaplanmadı</div><div class="grade">1,00 üzerinden puanlanmış</div><div class="questionflag editable" id="yui_3_18_1_1_1767644350614_774"><input type="hidden" name="q21665:127_:flagged" value="0"><input type="hidden" value="qaid=531021&amp;qubaid=21665&amp;qid=11578&amp;slot=127&amp;checksum=e81045a0a8aec60fb2dd47355a38c1e8&amp;sesskey=bsAI63OWde&amp;newstate=" class="questionflagpostdata">
<input type="hidden" class="questionflagvalue" id="q21665:127_:flaggedcheckbox" name="q21665:127_:flagged" value="0"><a tabindex="0" class="aabtn" role="button" aria-pressed="false" aria-label="İşaretli" title="İlerisi için bu soruyu işaretle"><img class="questionflagimage" src="https://online-learning2025-2026.gidatarim.edu.tr/theme/image.php/academi/core/1762167339/i/unflagged" alt="">Soruyu işaretle</a></div></div><div class="content"><div class="formulation clearfix"><h4 class="accesshide">Soru metini</h4><input type="hidden" name="q21665:127_:sequencecheck" value="2"><div class="qtext"><div class="clearfix"><p>When a system is built specially by a supplier, why is the requirements specification often considered both a technical and a legal document?</p></div></div><fieldset class="ablock no-overflow visual-scroll-x"><legend class="prompt h6 fw-normal "><span class="visually-hidden">Soru 127</span> Lütfen birini seçin:</legend><div class="answer"><div class="r0"><input type="radio" name="q21665:127_answer" disabled="disabled" value="0" id="q21665:127_answer0" aria-labelledby="q21665:127_answer0_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:127_answer0_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">a. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">Because off-the-shelf systems require detailed requirements to be used.</div></div> </div>
<div class="r1"><input type="radio" name="q21665:127_answer" disabled="disabled" value="1" id="q21665:127_answer1" aria-labelledby="q21665:127_answer1_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:127_answer1_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">b. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">Because the specification is part of the development contract, defining what the supplier must deliver and under what terms.</div></div> </div>
<div class="r0"><input type="radio" name="q21665:127_answer" disabled="disabled" value="2" id="q21665:127_answer2" aria-labelledby="q21665:127_answer2_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:127_answer2_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">c. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">Because requirements are always written by lawyers and never by engineers.</div></div> </div>
