<div class="r1"><input type="radio" name="q21665:165_answer" disabled="disabled" value="1" id="q21665:165_answer1" aria-labelledby="q21665:165_answer1_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:165_answer1_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">b. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">Because dynamic binding guarantees the same service instance is always used in every test.</div></div> </div>
<div class="r0"><input type="radio" name="q21665:165_answer" disabled="disabled" value="2" id="q21665:165_answer2" aria-labelledby="q21665:165_answer2_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:165_answer2_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">c. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">External services are 'black-boxes', may change, and their non-functional behavior can vary with load.</div></div> </div>
<div class="r1"><input type="radio" name="q21665:165_answer" disabled="disabled" value="3" id="q21665:165_answer3" aria-labelledby="q21665:165_answer3_label"><div class="d-flex w-auto" id="q21665:165_answer3_label" data-region="answer-label"><span class="answernumber">d. </span><div class="flex-fill ms-1">Because service testing is free of charge in all pay-per-use models.</div></div> </div>
